               <p>SARAH MOSS. I am a <rs id="t18280221-198-viclabel1056" type="occupation">stay-maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-198-victim1169 t18280221-198-viclabel1056"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18280221-198-crimeloc1057">Prospect-row, Kingsland</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280221-198-crimeloc1057" type="placeName" value="Prospect-row, Kingsland"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280221-198-crimeloc1057" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-198-off1054 t18280221-198-crimeloc1057"></join>. On the 15th of January I was in the parlour, I heard a noise, came into the shop, and saw the prisoner about two doors off, with something in his apron - I missed the stays from the window; I was too ill to follow him, and he got away; I am sure he is the boy - I saw him again on the Saturday.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-198-person1170">
                  ANN 
                  SARAH BARLOW
               <interp inst="t18280221-198-person1170" type="surname" value="SARAH BARLOW"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-198-person1170" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-198-person1170" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner came to me on the morning of the 15th, to my shop, which is a quarter of a mile from Moss' - he asked the price of tulip roots - I told him 4d. each - he went out, but came in soon after, and took a hyacinth glass from the window - I took it from him, and found these stays in his apron; he said he brought them from his aunt's, at Haggerston - I gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-198-person1171">
